:::summary
Ecology is the branch of biology that studies the relationships between living organisms and their environments — including relationships among organisms themselves and between organisms and the physical world. Founded as a distinct discipline in the nineteenth century, ecology addresses questions ranging from the interactions of individual organisms with their habitat to the functioning of entire biospheres. For Christians, ecology is inseparable from the doctrine of creation: God made the natural world, pronounced it good, and charged humanity with its faithful stewardship.
:::

